The paper presents a new data structure for the c-approximate near neighbor problem in Euclidean space, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and machine learning. The paper uses techniques from data structures, information theory, computational geometry, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
